<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="90" type="descriptions">
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="90">Descriptions.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="90">
Mostly annuals; stems with L-shaped hairs bearing elongate one-armed cap-cells. Leaves alternate. Inflorescence a thyrsoid panicle with corymbiform cymose branches bearing pedunculate heads or a single terminal head. Involucral bracts ca. 80 in ca, seven series, often with widely scarious margins and awns often black at tips; receptacles epaleaceous. Florets ca. 30 in a head; corollas whitish to purplish, basal tube long, narrowly funnelform distally, throat as long as the narrow glabrous lobes; anther bases plain, not tailed; apical appendage glabrous, with thin cell walls, sometimes weakly ornamented; style base with distinct annular node; branches with acicular sweeping hairs. Achenes 5 or 8-10-ribbed, setuliferous with setulae scarcely divided at tips, idioblasts present but not grouped, raphids elongate; pappus with copious barbellate setae, greenish, yellowish or tawny, rarely white, outer pappus short, squamiform. Chromosome number n = 9, 10 (
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, SB" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="79 - 84" publicationUrl="10.2307/2484281" refId="B21" refString="Jones, SB, 1979. Chromosomes of the Vernonieae (Compositae). Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 106: 79 - 84, DOI: 10.2307/2484281" title="Chromosomes of the Vernonieae (Compositae)." url="10.2307/2484281" volume="106" year="1979">Jones 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, SB" editor="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="119 - 128" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/1219710?seq=1page_scan_tab_contents" refId="B22" refString="Jones, SB, 1982. . In: Loeve, A, Ed., IOPB Chromosome number reports LXXIV. Taxon 31: 119 - 128, http://www.jstor.org/stable/1219710?seq=1page_scan_tab_contents" url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/1219710?seq=1page_scan_tab_contents" volume="31" volumeTitle="IOPB Chromosome number reports LXXIV." year="1982">1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ayodele, MS" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium" pageId="49" pageNumber="98" pagination="7 - 8" publicationUrl="10.1002/fedr.19991100715" refId="B3" refString="Ayodele, MS, 1999. Karyomorphological studies in some Nigerian species of Vernonia Schreb. (Asteraceae) with different growth forms. Feddes Repertorium 110: 7 - 8, DOI: 10.1002/fedr.19991100715" title="Karyomorphological studies in some Nigerian species of Vernonia Schreb. (Asteraceae) with different growth forms." url="10.1002/fedr.19991100715" volume="110" year="1999">Ayodele 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="90">
Pollen lophate with ca. 32 lacunae, with five or more pores that seem to be rather asymmetrically distributed on the grains; the pores occur in lacunae that, in a few cases, are adjacent; margins of muri minutely echinate to psilate, without micropunctations, baculae closely spaced in single evenly spaced row under each murus, baculae in turn subtended by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“rhizomate”">&quot;rhizomate&quot;</normalizedToken>
structure that is weakly attached to the footlayer, the muri thus easily stripping away from the footlayer (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Scanning electron micrographs of Polydora angustifolia (Steetz) H, Rob. A Intact grain with visible pore B Intact grain with 2 visible pores in adjacent lacunae C Grain with muri partially removed showing distorted inner surface and five pores, one pore on opposite surface visible through torn area. A from Brass 16090 B, C from Christensen &amp; Patel 1457. Views from Robinson &amp; Skvarla, PhytoKeys 2014." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.60.6734.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/77494" pageId="41" pageNumber="90">22 C</figureCitation>
). The pollen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fenzl" authorityYear="1844" class="Polychaeta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Polydora" order="Asterales" pageId="41" pageNumber="90" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="90">Polydora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proves to have a lophate condition with well-defined lophae or muro bearing 4-5 spinules on each segment. The lophae are subtended by columellae in a single series not leaving an ogee-shaped gap in the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="90">
Notable secondary metabolites: sesquiterpene lactone glaucolides/hirsutanolies (
<bibRefCitation author="Bohlmann, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="3 - 43" publicationUrl="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" refId="B5" refString="Bohlmann, F, Jakupovic, J, 1990. Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae). Plant Systematics and Evolution 4: 3 - 43, DOI: 10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" title="Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae)." url="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" volume="4" year="1990">Bohlmann and Jakupovic 1990</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia poskeana" order="Asterales" pageId="41" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poskeana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="90">Vernonia poskeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vatke &amp; Hildebr.), elemanolides, eudesmanolides, secoglaucolides (
<bibRefCitation author="Herz, W" editor="Hind, DJN" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="229 - 251" refId="B14" refString="Herz, W, 1996. A review of the terpenoid chemistry of the Vernonieae. In: Hind, DJN, Beentje, HJ, Eds., Compositae: Systematics. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew: 229 - 251" title="A review of the terpenoid chemistry of the Vernonieae." volumeTitle="Compositae: Systematics." year="1996">Herz 1996</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia poskeana" order="Asterales" pageId="41" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poskeana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="90">Vernonia poskeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vatke &amp; Hildebr.
</paragraph>
