<taxonomicName authorityName="Fenzl" authorityYear="1844" class="Polychaeta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="41" pageNumber="90" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(Steetz in Peters 1864). The generic name 
<taxonomicName genus="Crystalopollen" lsidName="Crystalopollen" pageId="41" pageNumber="90" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="90">Crystalopollen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on the lophate pattern of the pollen observed by Steetz.
